Key Learning Points
Redirects do not guarantee security.
Browsers hide intermediate responses.
Burp Suite reveals everything transmitted over HTTP.
Always inspect response bodies, even for 3xx status codes.
Pentester's Perspective
Never assume a redirect means the request failed securely.

Always inspect the complete raw response. Sensitive information can be leaked before the browser follows the redirect, making this a common source of information disclosure during penetration tests.

